@Node "INSTALLATION" "doc/NerveEX.guide/INSTALLATION"
@Next "NERVEEXPREFS"
@Prev "INTRODUCTION"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}2. INSTALLATION@{ub}

NerveEX  requires  at  least  OS2.04 to run. NerveEX is very simple to
install.

Use  the  installer  script  or execute the following steps to install
NerveEX:

- Copy @{"NerveEX" Link "NERVEEX"} and @{"NerveEXPrefs" Link "NERVEEXPREFS"} to your preferred path for utilities.
- Copy NerveEX.prefs to ENVARC: or generate your own preferences file.

Now  change  the  preferences  file at will and enjoy programs without
being bothered by annoying requesters.

@EndNode

@Node "NERVEEXPREFS" "doc/NerveEX.guide/NERVEEXPREFS"
@Next "DEBUG"
@Prev "INSTALLATION"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3. NERVEEXPREFS@{ub}

In  order  to  enter  all  the settings that are needed for NerveEX to
work,  there's  a  GUI  provided  with  the program.  NEVER modify the
configuration file generated by NerveEXPrefs by hand.  If this file is
not what it's supposed to be, NerveEX may crash or not work properly.

Here's a description of the gadgets and what they do:

   _______________________________________________________________ ...
  |  |
  |  |--@{"   " Link "BOX"} @{"Library" Link "LIBRARY"}
  |  |   |
  |  |   |--@{"   " Link "BOX"} @{"Function" Link "FUNCTION"}
  |  |   |   |
  |  |   |    --@{"   " Link "BOX"} @{"Task" Link "TASK"}
  |  |   |        |
  |  |   |         --@{"   " Link "BOX"} @{"Structure" Link "STRUCTURE"}
  |  |   |             |
  |  |   |              --@{"   " Link "BOX"} @{"Member" Link "MEMBER"}
  |  |   |                  |
  |  |   |                   --@{"   " Link "BOX"} @{"Identification" Link "IDENTIFICATION"}
  |  |   |   ___
  |  |    --|___| Function
  |  |   ___
  |  |--|___| Library
  |  |    |
  |  .    .
  | etc.
  |_______________________________________________________________ ...
   __________________________________________
  |__________________________________________| @{"New Level" Link "GD_NEW_LEVEL"} @{"Add" Link "GD_ADD"} @{"Del" Link "GD_DEL"}
   _____________________________   _____________________   ___________
  |______Stringgadget1__________| |____Stringgadget2____| |Cyclegadget|
  

Here's a description of the advanced menu items and what they do:

- @{"Font" Link "MN_FONT"}
- @{"Trace calls" Link "MN_TRACE"}

All  the  other  menu  items  are  standard menu items and need not be
explained further.

@EndNode

@Node "LIBRARY" "doc/NerveEX.guide/LIBRARY"
@Next "FUNCTION"
@Prev "NERVEEXPREFS"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.1 Library@{ub}

This  entry  let's  you  define  the  library  in  which the following
functions will be patched.  This entry MUST end with ".library".

Example: "intuition.library"


See @{"technical description" Link "TECHNICAL_DES"} for more details.

@EndNode

@Node "FUNCTION" "doc/NerveEX.guide/FUNCTION"
@Next "TASK"
@Prev "LIBRARY"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.2 Function@{ub}

This  entry  let's  you define the function which you want to patch in
the  library  entered  above.   To do so you must enter the offset for
this   function.    The   offset  will  be  automatically  scanned  by
NerveEXPrefs  if you have installed fd-files on your harddisk and made
an  "assign  FD:"  to this directory.  The offset has to be entered in
the "Stringgadget2".

Example: "EasyRequestArgs"         Stringgadget2(Offset): "0x024C"


See @{"technical description" Link "TECHNICAL_DES"} for more details.

@EndNode

@Node "TASK" "doc/NerveEX.guide/TASK"
@Next "STRUCTURE"
@Prev "FUNCTION"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.3 Task@{ub}

This entry defines the task for which the following entries are valid.

Example: "#?"   for all tasks or  "#?MyName#?" for a special task.


See @{"technical description" Link "TECHNICAL_DES"} for more details.

@EndNode

@Node "STRUCTURE" "doc/NerveEX.guide/STRUCTURE"
@Next "MEMBER"
@Prev "TASK"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.4 Structure@{ub}

This  entry  defines the structure for which the following entries are
valid.

Example: "EasyRequest"

This entry is only for clarity.  NerveEX doesn't use it.  But you have
to  enter  the  register,  which  contains  the  base  address of this
structure.   This register has to be entered in the Stringgadget2.  In
contrast to the structure name this entry is mandatory.

Example: "A1"


See @{"technical description" Link "TECHNICAL_DES"} for more details.

@EndNode

@Node "MEMBER" "doc/NerveEX.guide/MEMBER"
@Prev "STRUCTURE"
@Next "IDENTIFICATION"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.5 Member@{ub}

This entry defines the member of the above entered structure.

TEMPLATE: [<name>] {(<integer-value>)} [[<name>] {(<integer-value>)} ...]


Example:

The  register points to (struct Window *) and we want to reference the
title text of the screen:

  "Window(46)->WScreen.Title(22)"
   or
   "(46)(22)"
   or
   "Enterprise(46)NC1701D(22)Warp"

1. Window(46) or (46)         points to "struct Screen *"
2. ->Screen.Title(22) or (22) points to "UBYTE *Title"

The name between the closing and opening parentheses is not necessary.
Incorrect entries are not accepted.  The entry cannot be enabled until
it is entered correctly.

The "Cycle gadget" defines what type of pointer the entry represents:

- '*String'  : Pointer to a string.
- '*Hex'     : Pointer to hexadecimal value.
- 'Hex'      : The register contains the value itself.


See @{"technical description" Link "TECHNICAL_DES"} for more details.

@EndNode

@Node "IDENTIFICATION" "doc/NerveEX.guide/IDENTIFICATION"
@Prev "MEMBER"
@Next "GD_NEW_LEVEL"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.6 Identification@{ub}

This  entry  defines  the  name  or  hexadecimal value which the above
member points to.


See @{"technical description" Link "TECHNICAL_DES"} for more details.


@EndNode

@Node "GD_NEW_LEVEL" "doc/NerveEX.guide/GD_NEW_LEVEL"
@Prev "MEMBER"
@Next "GD_ADD"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.7 New Level@{ub}

Clicking this button creates a new entry.  This entry will be inserted
as child of the current one.

@EndNode

@Node "GD_ADD" "doc/NerveEX.guide/GD_ADD"
@Prev "GD_NEW_LEVEL"
@Next "GD_DEL"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.8 Add@{ub}

Clicking this button creates a new entry.  This entry will be inserted
behind the current entry on the same level.

@EndNode

@Node "GD_DEL" "doc/NerveEX.guide/GD_DEL"
@Prev "GD_ADD"
@Next "BOX"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.9 Del@{ub}

The "Del" button deletes the current entry and all its children.

@EndNode

@Node "BOX" "doc/NerveEX.guide/BOX"
@Prev "GD_DEL"
@Next "MN_FONT"
@Toc "Main"

@{b}3.1.10 Clickbox@{ub}

Double-clicking  the  checkbox expands or shrinks all children of this
entry.  Double-clicking the text enables or disables the entry.

@EndNode

